net.varkhan.base.containers
Class SyncIndexedContainer<Type>

java.lang.Object
  net.varkhan.base.containers.SyncIndexedContainer<Type>
Type Parameters:
Type - the type of elements in the container
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable, Container<Type>, Indexable, Indexed<Type>, IndexedContainer<Type>, IndexedVisitable<Type>, Visitable<Type>
public abstract class SyncIndexedContainer<Type>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IndexedContainer<Type>, java.io.Serializable

Provide multithread safety over an unsynchronized IndexedContainer implementation

This class wraps an unsynchronized IndexedContainer implementation in a read/write synchronized layer, provided all read operations on the underlying container are state-less (i.e. do not modify any field data in the container).

Individual read access to container items is thread safe, and iterators are fail-fast, meaning they will throw a ConcurrentModificationException whenever is detected a modification on the underlying container that is not the result of the iterator's own methods.

A pair of read/write locks is provided to classes extending this implementation, allowing them to protect write operations from concurrent access, and read operations from inconsistent state during the writes.

Note that since an IndexedContainer is read-only, no specific thread-safety is provided by this implementation, unless it is subclassed to wrap writable container types using the appropriate locking.
